# AICP v51 — Protocol Backlog from Consumer Use-Case Needs

> Scope: **protocol only** (Core + extensions + registries + schemas + fixtures + conformance + profiles).  
> Out of scope: platform/enforcer implementations, chat UX, agent internals.

This backlog translates the five consumer needs (brand-safe public agent chat; enterprise service-chaining; reception chat as PaaS; auth provider; agent-agent automation) into **missing protocol capabilities** in the current repo state (AICP-main_v51).

## Conventions
- **Productized extension/message** = has: (1) RFC doc, (2) schema(s), (3) registry entries, (4) fixtures, (5) conformance suite(s), and (6) profile wiring (if claimed as interoperable bundle).
- **Option** = selectable via `contract.ext.*` (or profile requirement). If enabled, MUST be machine-checkable.
- **Namespacing**: keep vendor-specific values as `vendor:*` or `org:*` where appropriate.

## Priority order (recommended)
P0 = adoption blockers / interop integrity; P1 = enterprise chain foundations; P2 = ops/security/interop hygiene; P3 = profile packaging.


