- `conformance/core/CT_CORE_0.1.json (extend `payload_schema_map` for `ERROR`, or add new suite `ER_ERROR_0.1.json`)`
- `registry/message_types.json (ensure `ERROR` spec_ref points to concrete section + status remains stable)`
- `docs/core/AICP_Core_v0.1_Normative.md and/or `docs/suite/...` (add normative ERROR payload definition if missing)`

### Conformance & fixtures
- If added to CT_CORE_0.1: include `CN-PAYLOAD-SCHEMA-01`-style check for ERROR via payload_schema_map.
- Add at least one negative fixture: malformed ERROR without `error_code` should fail payload schema check.

