## P0.2 — New extension: `EXT-PARTICIPANTS` (membership/roles) with **two selectable models**

### Goal
Standardize multi-party session membership and role assignment so a validator can prove who is a participant and with what role(s). Support two options: (A) shared contract per session, (B) per-participant acceptance.

### Why (consumer need)
Use-cases 1/3/5 require user agents joining a moderated chat. Without protocol-level membership, implementers will invent incompatible join/leave semantics, undermining enforcement guarantees and auditability.

### Deliverables

- Extension ID registration: `EXT-PARTICIPANTS`.
- Message types: `PARTICIPANT_JOIN`, `PARTICIPANT_ACCEPT`, `PARTICIPANT_LEAVE`, optional `PARTICIPANT_UPDATE_ACCEPTANCE`.
- Payload schema defining: party_id (agent id), requested/assigned roles, acceptance authority, and which contract/version is accepted.
- Contract option: `contract.ext.participants.model: "shared" | "per_participant"`.
  - shared: acceptance binds to session contract.
  - per_participant: acceptance binds to participant-specific contract_ref/hash; messages must be compatible with sender acceptance.
- Conformance suite implementing normative invariants (see below).

### Files to add
- `docs/extensions/RFC_EXT_PARTICIPANTS.md`
- `schemas/extensions/ext-participants-payloads.schema.json`
- `conformance/extensions/PT_PARTICIPANTS_0.1.json`
- `fixtures/extensions/participants/PT-01_shared_model_happy.jsonl`
- `fixtures/extensions/participants/PT-02_per_participant_happy.jsonl`
- `fixtures/extensions/participants/PT-03_unaccepted_sender_expected_fail.jsonl`

### Files to modify
- `registry/extension_ids.json (add EXT-PARTICIPANTS)`
- `registry/message_types.json (add participant message types, mark experimental or stable as appropriate)`
- `docs/profiles/AICP_Profiles.md (add planned profile wiring; see P3 tasks)`

### Conformance & fixtures
- Add new runner checks:
  - `PT-MEMBERSHIP-01`: messages from a participant MUST occur after `PARTICIPANT_ACCEPT`.
  - `PT-ROLES-01`: if contract defines roles, assigned roles MUST be subset and MUST be checkable.
  - `PT-CONTRACT-BIND-01`: shared vs per_participant invariants.

- Sequence expectations in PT suite transcripts (like ENF suite does).

### Acceptance criteria
- `make validate` passes (including productization gate).
- `make conformance-ext` passes and includes the new PT suite.
- Negative fixture fails with `PT-MEMBERSHIP-01` (or schema) as expected.

### Notes
- Keep identity/auth provider out of scope here; party_id can be an opaque agent identifier. Identity lifecycle is handled in P1 tasks.
- Role strings should stay compatible with existing `contract.roles`.

