## P2.3 — Contract/context versioning conformance: enforce `vN` format + monotonicity + base/head invariants

### Goal
Make context evolution and conflict resolution predictable across implementations by adding explicit versioning rules to conformance.

### Why (consumer need)
Use-case 2/5: multi-agent workflows depend on consistent context/head_version semantics; otherwise agents diverge silently.

### Deliverables

- Normative rules (core or profile):
  - version format `vN` (N integer >= 1)
  - `CONTEXT_AMEND` increments head_version
  - base_version must equal previous head_version for linear history
  - fork/conflict must be resolved via `RESOLVE_CONFLICT` with defined behavior
- Fixtures demonstrating v1→v2→v3 progression and a fork resolution.
- Conformance checks enforcing these invariants.

### Files to add
- `fixtures/core/VS-01_version_progression.jsonl`
- `fixtures/core/VS-02_fork_and_resolve.jsonl`

### Files to modify
